1. *Gradonačelnik* je otvorio novu školu u gradu. (The *mayor* opened a new school in the city.)
2. Novi *gradonačelnik* je izabran nakon izbora. (The new *mayor* was elected after the election.)
3. Danas se sastajemo s *gradonačelnikom* kako bismo razgovarali o urbanizmu. (Today we are meeting with the *mayor* to discuss urban planning.)
4. Život u gradu zavisi od odluka koje donosi *gradonačelnik*. (Life in the city depends on the decisions made by the *mayor*.)
5. *Gradonačelnik* je najviši predstavnik grada. (The *mayor* is the highest representative of the city.)
6. U susret izborima za *gradonačelnika*, kandidati se obraćaju građanima. (In the run-up to the mayoral elections, candidates address the citizens.)
7. *Gradonačelnikova* odluka o gradnji mosta je izazvala polemiku. (The *mayor's* decision to build a bridge has sparked controversy.)
8. *Gradonačelnikov* govor je bio inspirativan i ohrabrujući. (The *mayor's* speech was inspiring and encouraging.)
9. *Gradonačelniku* je uručena nagrada za doprinos razvoju grada. (The *mayor* was awarded for his contribution to the development of the city.)
10. Gradski odbornici su kritikovali *gradonačelnika* zbog nedostatka transparentnosti u radu. (City councilors criticized the *mayor* for the lack of transparency in his work.)